      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Dean of the faculty, Cornell Law School.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Includes correspondence pertaining to a course on patent law at Cornell, 1907-1908; correpondence between Irvine and other law school administrators in New York State, primarily concerning the New York Association of Law Instructors and its interest in the examination for and admission to the New York State Bar; minutes of a meeting of the association; and copies of speeches and other printed material.</p>
      </scopecontent>
